{"key":"processedPost-11579192","value":{"id":11579192,"first":11577482,"last":11579192,"when":1259891949,"utime":"12/04/09 03:59 AM","content":"I now have four 75X sterilizers, a 921 and a 941.&nbsp; The 941 is too heavy for most stoves, unless you still have a good stove made in the 80's or earlier.<br /><br />I start the 75X with hot water, and as said above, allow it to preheat while you're preparing your jars or whatever.&nbsp; By the time you load the unit, you want the water boiling, and pressure will be reached much sooner.<br /><br />I'd go for the 75X, and then order a new burner and thermostat, plus a new blowout plug, relief valve and toggle valve.&nbsp; This way, you'll have a good stock of spare parts, and it's still half the price of a new unit.<br />RR","title":"Re: All American 75x or 941?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}